CatDescriptText: Jean Felix, student, Whitehall and Linda Myers, student, Pleasant Hills, were part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, May 6, 1961, pg. 7 with question: "Which of these reasons do you believe is the cause of many citizens not voting: (1) Belief that 'political machine-backed' candidates are hard to defeat? (2) Lack of interest in who runs their government?" Ms. Felix's answer reads: "I think the first reason is because people are interested mostly in who's in office."  Ms. Myers' answer reads: "The first one, because I believe most people think they will just leave it up to the other people."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Jean Felix wearing light colored head scarf, lion print blouse, and coat with striped trim on collar, holding item with image of male basketball player, standing on sidewalk in front of building with plaque that reads "Lutheran Church [Sup]ply Store"; Portrait of Linda Myers wearing dark head scarf, four strand necklace, and light colored coat, holding books in left arm, standing on corner of Wood Street and Liberty Avenue in front of window with RAAB Clothes sign reflection
